  "body": "So I finally know what the difference/problem is between nethermind and the others.\r\nNethermind returns keccak(blocknumber) as blockhash for every number.\r\nOthers return keccak(blocknumber) only for \"available blocks\" which means it returns keccak(blocknumber) only for blocknumber 0, all others are returned as 0\r\nI think your TestBlockhashProviders should implement this logic too: https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/1d2f21ba04d4fd14cada95479d57b8d368b70af7/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Blockchain/BlockhashProvider.cs#L41\r\nThis would mean we could finally test the clients against each other without having a failure whenever the BLOCKHASH opcode is executed",
